---
export const prerender = true;
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Privacy — ActivityRadar"
  description="How ActivityRadar collects and uses data."
>
  <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-4 py-14">
    <h1 class="text-2xl font-bold text-navy mb-8">Privacy</h1>

    <div class="prose-content text-navy/80 leading-relaxed flex flex-col gap-6">

      <section>
        <p>
          ActivityRadar is a directory of youth activity organizations in the Puget Sound region.
          We collect a small amount of data — only what we need to run the site.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-semibold text-navy text-base mb-3">What we collect</h2>
        <p class="mb-3">
          <strong>Claim and suggestion submissions.</strong> When you claim a listing or suggest
          an organization, we collect your name and email address (and, optionally, your role and
          any notes you add). This goes into our database so we can review and respond to your
          request. We use it for no other purpose.
        </p>
        <p class="mb-3">
          <strong>Search events.</strong> When you search, we log the query, filters, and result
          count. We do not log your IP address or link searches to an individual. This data tells
          us where the directory has gaps so we can add more organizations.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Aggregate traffic data</strong> via Cloudflare Web Analytics. Page views,
          referrer, and country — no cookies, no individual tracking, no advertising profiles.
          Cloudflare processes this data on our behalf and does not sell it.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-semibold text-navy text-base mb-3">What we do not collect</h2>
        <p>
          No user accounts. No passwords. No payment information. No device fingerprints.
          No advertising IDs. No cross-site tracking pixels. No behavioral data.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-semibold text-navy text-base mb-3">Who sees your data</h2>
        <p>
          Cloudflare runs the hosting, database, and analytics infrastructure. They do not sell
          customer data. No other third party receives data from this site.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          We do not sell personal information and never have.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-semibold text-navy text-base mb-3">How long we keep it</h2>
        <p>
          Claim and suggestion records: kept until the request is resolved, then archived
          for 12 months and deleted. Search events: 90 days. Analytics: 30 days (Cloudflare).
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-semibold text-navy text-base mb-3">Your rights</h2>
        <p>
          You can ask us what we hold about you, ask us to correct it, or ask us to delete it.
          Email <a href="mailto:jeffthomas@pugetsound.edu" class="text-rust hover:underline">jeffthomas@pugetsound.edu</a>
          and we will handle it within 30 days.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-semibold text-navy text-base mb-3">Children</h2>
        <p>
          ActivityRadar is for parents finding youth activities. We do not knowingly collect
          information from children under 13.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-semibold text-navy text-base mb-3">Contact</h2>
        <p>
          ActivityRadar is published by Field &amp; Forge Ventures.
          Questions: <a href="mailto:jeffthomas@pugetsound.edu" class="text-rust hover:underline">jeffthomas@pugetsound.edu</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

    </div>
  </div>
</Base>
